      "writtenOn": "2026-03-30T06:55:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For safer, size of buffer can keep as per inotify manpage, it says:\n\nSpecifying a buffer of size `sizeof(struct inotify_event) + NAME_MAX + 1` will be sufficient to read at least one event.\n\nReference : https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/inotify.7.html",
      "revId": "8ff14b44457d8b19147e9df2832cf47375872b61",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f82796fd_d424fd4b",
        "filename": "log_manager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 808,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002680
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-31T08:22:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My thinking here was to use a larger buffer so one callback can drain multiple queued inotify events, instead of processing only one event per iteration. Since this runs under sdeventplus, a smaller buffer would still be functionally correct because the callback will continue firing while the fd remains readable, but it may require more iterations during bursts of synced files (for example, during full sync) i was mainly thinking about the performance side here.",
      "parentUuid": "476d18ad_95ccb3c4",
      "revId": "8ff14b44457d8b19147e9df2832cf47375872b61",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c7931f1_fc48a6fc",
        "filename": "log_manager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 808,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001993
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-06T04:49:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Haa got it, that\u0027s good..\n\nI hope bigger buffer wont cause partial read of events.",
      "parentUuid": "f82796fd_d424fd4b",
      "revId": "8ff14b44457d8b19147e9df2832cf47375872b61",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4f3241ae_debe69bd",
        "filename": "log_manager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
