      "author": {
        "id": 1000427
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-06T10:31:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes it should be always buffer_size / event_size.",
      "parentUuid": "1c7931f1_fc48a6fc",
      "revId": "8ff14b44457d8b19147e9df2832cf47375872b61",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aa8261e4_7e7425d2",
        "filename": "log_manager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 808,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002680
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-08T08:50:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure. Based on the man page, `sizeof(struct inotify_event) + NAME_MAX + 1` is about 272 bytes, which is enough for one worst-case event.\n\nSo I can keep the buffer at `65280` bytes. In the worst case, that gives room for about 240 events in a single read.",
      "parentUuid": "4f3241ae_debe69bd",
      "revId": "8ff14b44457d8b19147e9df2832cf47375872b61",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
